{"primary_mode":"summaries","declared_mode":"summaries","edit_format":"structured_edits","secondary_modes":["topk"],"rationale":"The current run is still improving after removing regularization, so the next low-complexity probe is a gentler step schedule: add a short warmup and a nonzero cosine floor to avoid decaying too aggressively over the fixed step budget.","edits":[{"op":"replace_function","function":"build_scheduler","old":"","new":"","anchor":"","text":"","source":"def build_scheduler(optimizer: optim.Optimizer, steps_per_epoch: int):
    if not USE_LR_SCHEDULE:
